  "prompt": "What are some mind-blowing tech tools that most people don't know about?",
  "response": "Sure, here are some lesser-known but mind-blowing tech tools that you might find interesting:\n\n1. **Notion**: While increasingly popular, some may not be aware that it's more than just a note-taking app. It's a versatile productivity tool that combines databases, task management, and collaboration features.\n\n2. **Roam Research**: A unique note-taking tool designed for networked thought, ideal for researchers, writers, and anyone who benefits from linking their ideas in a non-linear way.\n\n3. **Obsidian**: Another powerful note-taking app that uses markdown files and allows for complex linking and graph views, which is perfect for creating your own knowledge graph.\n\n4. **Trello**: This project management tool uses boards, lists, and cards to organize tasks and projects, and it's highly customizable with automation and integrations.\n\n5. **Zotero**: An excellent research tool for organizing citations, bibliographies, and research materials.\n\n6. **Miro**: An online collaborative whiteboard platform that enables teams to ideate, brainstorm, and plan visually.\n\n7. **Streak**: A CRM tool integrated directly into Gmail, turning your email inbox into a powerful workspace for managing relationships and deals.\n\n8. **Sublime Text**: While well-known among developers, it's an incredibly efficient and versatile text editor with a vast array of plugins and customization options.\n\n9. **Jitsi Meet**: An open-source video conferencing platform that offers secure, fully encrypted calls and requires no installations or accounts to use.\n\n10. **Toggl**: A super simple but effective time-tracking tool that helps both individuals and teams track time across various projects accurately.\n\n11. **DALL-E/DALL-E 2**: AI tools from OpenAI that generate images from textual descriptions, showcasing powerful advancements in visual AI.\n\n12. **Descript**: A multimedia editing tool that allows you to edit videos and podcasts using text rather than traditional timelines.\n\n13. **Figma**: A collaborative interface design tool that's gaining traction for its ability to enable real-time collaboration on design projects.\n\n14. **Mullvad VPN**: Known for its strong stance on privacy and simplicity, this VPN service protects your internet connection with minimal fuss.\n\n15. **TinyPNG**: A web-based tool for compressing images without losing quality, optimizing them for faster web performance.\n\nThese tools can significantly enhance productivity, creativity, and collaboration in various fields. Explore them to see how they can fit into your workflow!",
